FT  13 MAY 91 / US Treasury clears British company
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A BRITISH company blacklisted by the US Treasury as a suspected agent of the
Iraqi government was yesterday cleared of suspicion and allowed to continue
trading with American corporations.
Sollatek, an electronics company based in London, is the fourth organisation
named by the Treasury's Office of Foreign Assets Control on April 1 to have
been issued with a licence pending its removal from the blacklist.
The action follows discussions with officials at the UK Department of Trade
and Industry. PMK, Qudos and Liverpool Polytechnic were granted similar
licences last week.
Mr Manhal Allos, director, said last night he had not ruled out legal action
against the US government.
