<HEADLINE>
FT  13 MAY 91 / Letter: Bank's role
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr ROBIN HUTTENBACH.
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, As the director of a small company that would not be in business
without the help my bank has given me over the years, I think that Mr F X
O'Malley (Letters, May 2) is wrong in suggesting that managers should visit
their customers.
Surely his time and that of his bank manager would be better employed by
making sure that he regularly updates his company's cash flow and any other
financial projections deemed necessary. From my experience, this should be
done at least once a month and the information then forwarded to the bank
manager for review. Far from being a subjective approach, this is the best
method I know for detecting problems at an early stage.
Robin Huttenbach,
Nelson Design,
Southbank Technopark,
90 London Road, SE1
</TEXT>
