<HEADLINE>
FT  13 MAY 91 / Survey of Cardiff (5): A Welsh song for Europe
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTHONY MORETON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THIS IS Europe Week in Cardiff. The festival is a promotion of Europe within
the Welsh capital and, in particular, of the city's place within Europe.
It sees French fashion, German food, Italian music, opera from the Welsh
National Opera Company - and, this being Wales, a rugby festival.
Cardiff is Europe's youngest capital, created in 1955. Although twinned with
Stuttgart and Nantes, it has not had particularly strong links with
continental Europe since its coal trade collapsed after the second world
war.
'This festival,' says Roger Paine, the city's chief executive, 'is intended
to raise the importance of Europe within Cardiff. In doing that, we want it
also to raise our profile within Europe.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
